AGI - The Gaza War >, the most bloody ever, broke out exactly six months ago, had a frightening human budget. At least 33.137 people were killed in the Palestinian territory besieged in the Israel Retaliation Campaign for the Hamas attack on October 7, according to the Ministry of Health in Gaza, managed by Hamas. The unprecedented Hamas raid in southern Israel killed 1,170 Israelis and foreigners, most of whom were civilians, according to an Afp count based on Israeli official data. While Hamas refused to say how many fighters he lost, Israel claims he killed more than 12,000.<br> Like many of the figures on the victims of the war, this is also impossible to independently confirm.
&nbsp;
- PERDITES IN ISRAELE? The Hamas attack on October 7 caused the death of 1,170 Israelis and foreigners, most of whom were civilians. The Israeli army has declared that it has lost some 600 soldiers since the beginning of the war, 260 of which have been killed in the same Gaza since it entered action on 27 October. Seventeen Israelis - soldiers, settlers and civilians - were killed in the violence in the West Bank occupied by Israel. Eight civilians and 10 Israeli soldiers died in the north due to missile attacks and Hezbollah rockets from Lebanon, with tens of thousands of displaced persons. Of the approximately 250 Israeli and foreign hostages kidnapped by Hamas on October 7, 129 remain in Gaza, of which 34 died according to the military. The bodies of 12 hostages were returned to Israel. The Israeli army has declared that since October 7, 9,100 rockets have been launched from Gaza. He recalled 300,000 reservists, 17% of whom are women.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
- PALESTINED PERDATA Most 33.137 people killed in Gaza in the Israeli retaliation campaign are women and children, according to the Ministry of Health of the territory. The Israeli army claims to have "eliminated" 12,000 enemy fighters, including five brigade commanders and 20 battalion commanders.<br> At least 459 Palestinians were killed in the violence in the occupied West Bank, according to the ministry of Health based in Ramallah. The Israeli army claims to have "eliminated 420 terrorists" in its operations in the West Bank. Israel claims to have struck 32,000 targets in Gaza since the beginning of the war.
&nbsp;
- LIBANON AND SIRIA><br> The Israeli fire from October killed at least 359 people in Lebanon, mostly Hezbollah fighters, while at least 70 civilians died, according to an Afp count. Cross-border fire has made tens of thousands of people displaced in southern Lebanon. The total includes also fighters from other Lebanese groups, including Hamas and the Amal movement, ally of Hezbollah. At least 23 Hezbollah fighters were killed in Israeli attacks in Syria, according to an AFP count, and seven Iranian revolutionary Guards were killed in an attack in Damascus last week.<br> Israel claims to have hit 1,400 air targets in Lebanon and 3,300 with artillery, rockets and tanks. The Israeli military declared that 3,100 rockets were launched across the border from Lebanon and 35 from Syria.&nbsp;
